        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 8 at 9:28AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 928 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Briscoe, or 19 miles east of Miami, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Briscoe.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
